snippet.textDisplay:
Momina Mustehsan (Urdu: مومنہ مستحسن‬‎) is a Pakistani singer-songwriter, musician and social activist. Mustehsan has become one of the most popular and high-profile celebrities of Pakistan.[1][2] In 2017, BBC named her one of the 100 most influential women, and the following year, Forbes featured her among its "30 Under 30" Asia list alongwith nine other Pakistani individuals.[3][4] That same year, Mustehsan was honored by the Stony Brook University–naming her among the "40 most successful graduates".[5]

Raised in Islamabad, Mustehsan earned a double majors degree in Biomedical Engineering and Applied Mathematics from the Stony Brook University.[6][7]   Curtsy Wikipedia....
